A single boundary marker from Mauretania Sitifensis records a demarcation, under Hadrian’s authority and “under the auspices” A unique formulation.  of L. Aelius Caesar, by the imperial procurator C. Petronius Celer between Regiae and an unidentified estate (the Saltus Cu[ --- ]). Celer’s capacity in this matter (whether provincial governor or financial procurator) is unclear; the next year he was serving as the provincial procurator in Mauretania Caesariensis, where he assigned boundaries to the Numidae “ex indulgentia” of the emperor Hadrian(Instance 

            73 (Elliott 2004)
      ).
